---
# Prompty sample for SweetLine highlighting
name: support-resolution-agent
displayName: Support Resolution Agent
description: |
  Produces concise customer support replies with policy grounding,
  tool awareness, and structured output for downstream review.
metadata:
  authors:
    - support-platform
    - prompt-quality
  tags: [customer-support, policy, triage]
  version: "2.1.0"
  owner: ${env:SUPPORT_PROMPTY_OWNER:prompt-team}
model:
  id: gpt-4o
  provider: foundry
  apiType: chat
  connection:
    kind: key
    endpoint: ${env:AZURE_OPENAI_ENDPOINT}
    apiKey: ${env:AZURE_OPENAI_API_KEY}
  options:
    temperature: 0.3
    maxOutputTokens: 1400
    topP: 0.9
inputs:
  - name: customerName
    kind: string
    description: Full name of the customer
    required: true
    example: Jane Doe
  - name: locale
    kind: string
    description: Preferred response locale
    default: en-US
    enumValues: [en-US, en-GB, fr-FR, de-DE]
  - name: ticket
    kind: object
    description: Ticket summary and normalized fields
    required: true
  - name: orderHistory
    kind: array
    description: Recent orders available to the assistant
    default: []
  - name: policyContext
    kind: string
    description: Policy text retrieved before rendering
    required: true
  - name: includeEscalation
    kind: boolean
    description: Whether escalation guidance should be shown
    default: false
outputs:
  - name: answer
    kind: string
    description: Final reply sent to the customer
  - name: sentiment
    kind: string
    enumValues: [positive, neutral, negative]
  - name: nextAction
    kind: string
    description: Internal next action for the support team
tools:
  - name: lookup_order
    kind: function
    description: Look up an order by identifier
    parameters:
      - name: orderId
        kind: string
        required: true
      - name: includeShipments
        kind: boolean
        default: true
  - name: policy_search
    kind: mcp
    serverName: support-policy-server
    connection:
      kind: reference
  - name: shipment_api
    kind: openapi
    specification: ${file:schemas/shipment.openapi.json}
    connection:
      kind: key
      endpoint: https://api.example.com/shipments
template:
  format: jinja2
  parser:
    kind: prompty-chat
sample:
  customerName: Jane Doe
  locale: en-US
  includeEscalation: true
  ticket:
    id: TCK-2048
    topic: delayed shipment
    urgency: high
    message: The tracking page has not moved for a week.
  orderHistory:
    - id: A100
      status: delayed
      date: 2026-05-13
    - id: A101
      status: delivered
      date: 2026-04-29
---
system:
# Support Reply Contract

You are a support assistant for Contoso Commerce.
Write in {{ locale }} and keep the reply direct, warm, and grounded.

Use only the policy context and ticket data supplied below.
Do not invent tracking events, compensation, or guarantees.

Policy context:

```text
{{ policyContext }}
```

Customer:

- Name: {{ customerName }}
- Ticket id: {{ ticket.id }}
- Topic: {{ ticket.topic }}
- Urgency: {{ ticket.urgency }}

{% if orderHistory %}
Recent orders:
{% for order in orderHistory %}
- Order #{{ order.id }} is {{ order.status }} as of {{ order.date }}.
{% endfor %}
{% else %}
No order history is available in the rendered context.
{% endif %}

{% if includeEscalation %}
Escalation guidance is enabled for this ticket.
{% else %}
Escalation guidance is disabled unless policy text requires it.
{% endif %}

assistant:
I will produce a customer-ready answer and an internal next action.

user:
Customer message:

> {{ ticket.message }}

Required response shape:

- Acknowledge the issue without blame.
- Cite the relevant policy in plain language.
- Mention the specific order only if it appears in the provided data.
- Offer one next action the support team can take.
- Avoid private implementation details.

{% set urgent_topics = ["delayed shipment", "missing item", "refund request"] %}
{% if ticket.topic in urgent_topics %}
Treat this as a priority support case.
{% endif %}

assistant:
Draft the reply using this Markdown structure:

**Hi {{ customerName }},**

Opening acknowledgement.

Policy-grounded explanation.

Next action:

- Concrete support action
- Customer-facing expectation

Internal review note:

```json
{
  "ticket": "{{ ticket.id }}",
  "topic": "{{ ticket.topic }}",
  "requires_escalation": {{ includeEscalation | lower }}
}
```

tool(policy_search):
Search the policy knowledge base for the topic `{{ ticket.topic }}`.

tool(lookup_order):
Use `{{ ticket.id }}` only as ticket context. Do not treat it as an order id.

developer:
Return a concise final answer. If policy information is insufficient, say what is missing and request a human review.
